description: Retrieve all of the protect configuration rule set number overrides that match the filters.

parameters.name: ProtectConfigurationId
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the protect configuration.

parameters.name: Filters
parameters.description: An array of ProtectConfigurationRuleSetNumberOverrideFilterItem objects to filter the results. (dict) --- The information for a protect configuration rule set number override that meets a specified criteria. The name of the attribute to filter on. An array values to filter for. (string) ---

nested_params.name: Name
nested_params.description: The name of the attribute to filter on.

nested_params.name: Values
nested_params.description: An array values to filter for.

nested_items.name: ProtectConfigurationArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the protect configuration.

nested_items.name: ProtectConfigurationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the protect configuration.

nested_items.name: DestinationPhoneNumber
nested_items.description: The destination phone number in E.164 format.

nested_items.name: CreatedTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time when the rule was created, in UNIX epoch time format.

nested_items.name: Action
nested_items.description: The action for the rule to perform of either blocking or allowing messages to the destination phone number.

nested_items.name: IsoCountryCode
nested_items.description: The two-character code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format, for the country or region.

nested_items.name: ExpirationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time the rule will expire at. If ExpirationTimestamp is not set then the rule will not expire.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to be used for the next set of paginated results. You don't need to supply a value for this field in the initial request.
